module.purpose:
This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the non-geometric representation of an electrical wire-harness assembly design including connectors, wires and cables and how they are connected. The information kept in a wiring harness assembly design can be associated to 3D and 2D geometry, including formboards. The specific elements and modules for electrical wire harness definition are:
AM for the abstract definition of complex shapes such as a typical connector interface independent of a particular connector part;
AM for the general definition of features on parts;
AM for the definition of terminals and conductors represented as transport features, on parts and part occurrences and how they are joined together to establish electrical nodes;
AM for the identification of terminals at the ends of wires and cables, including any intermediate terminals;
AM for the topology model of the harness nodes and segments;
AM for the hierarchical structure inside a harness segment;
in this AM, the application object is an
that brings together all needed parts for the design of an electrical wire harness such as connectors, contacts, wire, cables and coatings;
AM is extended to map:
the geometric representation of wires, cables and connectors to Edges and Vertices of the topological model;
the topological Edges and Vertices to the s of the associated s.
Overview of application modules specifically used for electrical wire harness definition
The AM Wiring_harness_assembly_design is created in such a way, that it can be used together with these geometric models:
AM as the most commonly used solid model, especially for rigid parts;
for the geometric representation of flexible segments with wires and cables the following models are most suitable:
AM as an effective description of a solid model, given by a cross sectional boundary shape that is swept along a centre curve with orientation in 3D space;
AM for a basic representation in 3D.
AM for a basic representation in 2D such a form board.
other geometric models can also be used.

inscope.li:
wire-list for an wiring harness assembly, consisting of:


wires and cables;

terminal lug;

terminal block;

electrically non conductive through termination;

wire cap;

single and multi pin connector contact;

splice definitions within the harness assembly;

electrical shielding definition in the assembly.

component-list for an wiring harness assembly, consisting of:


connector and associated material;

terminal lug;

terminal block;

electrically non conductive through termination;

wire cap;

single and multi pin connector contact;

splice definitions within the harness assembly;

electrical shielding definition in the assembly;

tape marking.

protection of harness segments including:


grommet;

retention clamps;

sleeving;

overall shielding for one or more harness segments.
